1. Arduino Pro Micro (5V, 16MHz)
2. MCP2515 CAN Bus Module
3. 6x N-channel MOSFETs (e.g., IRFZ44N or similar)
5. BLDC motor (e.g., T200 thruster)
6. 3x 10kΩ resistors (for back-EMF voltage dividers)
7. 3x 1kΩ resistors (for back-EMF voltage dividers)
8. Various capacitors (as per MOSFET driver requirements)
9. Heatsinks for MOSFETs
10. PCB or prototyping board
11. Wire (various gauges for signal and power like 12 gauge for power ish)
12. Power source (appropriate for your BLDC motor)
13. CAN bus termination resistor somewhere in your loop idk (120Ω)
14. Miscellaneous headers and connectors

Optional but recommended:
15. Cooling for MOSFETs
17. Current sense resistor and amplifier (for overcurrent protection)
18. TVS diodes (for transient voltage protection)
